Package org.forgerock.openam.session

Class SessionPropertyWhitelist

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.forgerock.openam.session.SessionPropertyWhitelist
  • @Singleton
public class SessionPropertyWhitelist
extends Object
    SessionPropertyWhitelist service that caches on a per-realm basis, and has listeners to update cached map if config changes.

    • Method Detail

      • getAllListedProperties

        public Set<String> getAllListedProperties​(String realm)
        Get the properties listed for the provided realm, using the caller token to check they have permission to see this result. This will return all properties that have been whitelisted, even those which may not be settable due to being protected properties.
        Parameters:
        realm - The realm in which this operation is taking place.
        Returns:
        The set of allowed listed properties.

      • isPropertyListed

        public boolean isPropertyListed​(SSOToken caller,
                                String realm,
                                Collection<String> propertyNames)
                         throws DelegationException,
                                SSOException
        Whether or not the property is listed in the whitelist. If the caller has permission to see a protected property they will, otherwise protected properties are removed from the returned set before being returned.
        Parameters:
        caller - The user checking their permission.
        realm - The realm in which this request is occurring.
        propertyNames - The names they wish for a response to.
        Returns:
        true if all requested properties are whitelisted.
        Throws:
        DelegationException
        SSOException

      • isPropertySetSettable

        public boolean isPropertySetSettable​(SSOToken caller,
                                     Collection<String> properties)
        Queries whether all the properties in the properties set are settable. Recording the key of the attempted setting. Returns true if all properties are settable, returns false if any one of them is not.
        Parameters:
        caller - The user checking their permission.
        properties - The property names they wish to set.
        Returns:
        true if all requested properties are settable.

      • isPropertyMapSettable

        public boolean isPropertyMapSettable​(SSOToken caller,
                                     Map<String,​String> properties)
        Queries whether all the properties in the properties map are settable, recording the key and value of the attempted setting. Returns true if all properties are settable, returns false if any one of them is not.
        Parameters:
        caller - The user checking their permission.
        properties - Map of property to value it wishes to be set to.
        Returns:
        true if all requested properties are settable.
